08/07/2007
NEW YORK, United States -- UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon called on Friday (July 6th) for "real engagement" between Greek Cypriots and Turkish Cypriots in order to reach a long-awaited settlement. Ban's call came ahead of the 1st anniversary of the sealing of the so-called July 8th accord between the two communities' leaders, Tassos Papadopoulos and Mehmet Ali Talat, who committed to restarting stalled negotiations on reunification. (UN website, CNA - 06/07/07)
